    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "After creating the dispatch source, use the methods of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.dispatch/documentation/Dispatch/DispatchSourceProtocol",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol to install the event handlers you need. The returned dispatch source is in the inactive state initially. When you are ready to begin processing events, call its ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.dispatch/documentation/Dispatch/DispatchObject/activate()",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To schedule timers, use the methods of the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.dispatch/documentation/Dispatch/DispatchSourceTimer",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol. You may schedule timers that fire once or fire multiple times. Each time the timer fires, the dispatch source calls your installed event handler.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
